sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as RHODS Operator<br/>controller-manager
    participant Components as Component Resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, CRs)

    Note over Admin,Components: Flow 1: Component Deployment via DataScienceCluster

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f dsc.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token/X.509
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event: DataScienceCluster created/updated<br/>In-process notification
    Operator->>K8sAPI: GET DataScienceCluster<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: DSC spec (components enabled)

    Operator->>Operator: Reconcile component manifests<br/>(kustomize + overlays)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply component manifests<br/>(Deployments, Services, CRs)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update DataScienceCluster status<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: kubectl get dsc shows status

    Note over Admin,Components: Flow 2: Platform Initialization via DSCInitialization

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Check for existing DSCI<br/>ServiceAccount Token (startup)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: DSCI exists or not found

    alt No DSCI exists
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create default DSCInitialization<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: DSCI created
    end

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply infrastructure resources<br/>(Namespaces, ServiceMeshMembers)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Infrastructure ready

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply monitoring configs<br/>(ServiceMonitors, PodMonitors)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Monitoring configured

    Note over Admin,Components: Flow 3: Monitoring Metrics Collection

    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>Cluster Monitoring
    participant MetricsSvc as controller-manager-metrics-service<br/>8443/TCP
    participant OpPod as Operator Pod<br/>8080/TCP

    Prom->>MetricsSvc: GET /metrics<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    MetricsSvc->>OpPod: Forward to 8080/TCP<br/>HTTP (internal)
    OpPod-->>MetricsSvc: Prometheus metrics
    MetricsSvc-->>Prom: Metrics response

    Note over Admin,Components: Flow 4: Legacy KfDef Migration

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f kfdef.yaml<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (legacy deployment)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event: KfDef detected
    Operator->>Operator: Upgrade Manager analyzes KfDef
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create equivalent DSC/DSCI<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: New CRs created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Mark KfDef as migrated<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: Migration complete
